page.title: 13St.Lawrences Church.
page.content: Saint Lawrence's Church was built in 1531.The present rector has been rector for two years.The church is black and white and is made of wood and plaster. In 1872 the Victorions built an extension at the front of the church. It consisted of two transepts and a chancel.They also put wooden supports on the sides of the church. Recently when work was being carried out on the roof it was found that these wooden supports were rotting so they were removed from the tower.This has left that part of the church very much as it was originally. The church was once called St.James' but a man called Mr.Gresswell changed it's name to St. Lawrence's.He did so because Denton Wakes fell on St. Lawrence's Day.
